org.neuroph.contrib.neat.gen
Class Organism

java.lang.Object
  org.neuroph.contrib.neat.gen.Organism
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, Innovation
public class Organism
extends java.lang.Object
implements Innovation, java.io.Serializable

An Organism is a member of the genetic population that is responsible for creating a NeuralNetowork. The Organism is also what is mutated and crossed-over when we need to evolve the population. An Organism contains a List of ConnectionGene and NeuronGene's as the representation of it's "genetic material".

Author:
Aidan Morgan

public void addNeuronGene(NeuronGene n)

public void addGene(Gene g)

copy

public Organism copy()
Creates an Identical copy of this Organism which will preserve the organism ID. This should only be used for creating identical duplicates. For any copying to be used inside NEAT, it is recommended that you use the copy(NeatParameters) method instead. Using this method from within NEAT will cause the SimpleSpeciator to fail. You have been warned.

Returns:
creates an Identical copy of this Organism which will preserve the organism ID.

getAncestory

public long[] getAncestory()
The array returned by this method contains the Organism id's that were used in the creation of this Organism. It is typically used for tracing the genetic history of this Organism.

Returns:
an array of organism id's which are the ancestors of this Organism.
